AIG Commercial Clients No Longer Expect Rate Cuts, Iglesias Says

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-06-02T15:14:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/aig-commercial-clients-no-longer-expect-rate-cuts-iglesias-says.html
American International Group Inc. (AIG) ,
the bailed-out insurer, said prices for business coverage have
stabilized after years of declines.  “We’re coming out of this phase of insureds going into the
market thinking they’re going to get a rate decrease,” said
Louis Iglesias, head of commercial casualty at AIG’s Chartis
division, in a conference sponsored by Advisen in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  